        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): write fallback dream diary on narrative timeout",
        "body": "## Summary\n- write a deterministic fallback `DREAMS.md` entry when dream narrative subagent runs time out, error, or return no assistant text\n- reuse the existing request-scoped fallback path so cron dreaming does not silently finish with phase artifacts but no dream diary entry\n- update the timeout regression test to assert that a fallback diary entry is persisted\n- add the required changelog entry for the user-facing Dream Diary fix\n- rebase on current `main` and resolve the `CHANGELOG.md` conflict\n\n## Context\nThis is a narrow follow-up to #74639 / #72546. It intentionally avoids the diary block/backfill structure handled in #70332 and focuses on the silent-success class where narrative generation is best-effort and can terminate without appending anything to `DREAMS.md`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Dream narrative terminal outcomes used to finish without appending `DREAMS.md`; after this patch, timeout and no-assistant-text outcomes write a deterministic fallback diary entry.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout of this PR head `8cdf94fca1` on Linux with Node `v22.22.2`, writing to fresh `/tmp/openclaw-pr78698-*` workspaces.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\ncd repos/openclaw\nnode --import tsx /tmp/pr78698-real-proof.mjs\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Copied terminal output from the run above:\n\n```text\ngit_head=8cdf94fca1\nnode=v22.22.2\n\n=== timeout-terminal-run ===\nworkspace=/tmp/openclaw-pr78698-timeout-terminal-run-sFydgt\ndreams_before=false\n[subagent] run sessionKey=dreaming-narrative-deep-5865f2fe5688-1778148000000 mode=default\n[subagent] waitForRun runId=proof-run-1 timeoutMs=60000\n[timeout-terminal-run] warn: memory-core: narrative generation ended with status=timeout for deep phase; writing fallback diary entry.\n[timeout-terminal-run] info: memory-core: narrative generation used fallback for deep phase because the narrative run ended with status=timeout.\n[subagent] deleteSession sessionKey=dreaming-narrative-deep-5865f2fe5688-1778148000000\ndreams_after=true\ndreams_bytes=172\ndiary_block_present=true\nfallback_entry_uses_phase_snippet=true\nsubagent_stats={\"runCalls\":1,\"waitCalls\":1,\"getMessagesCalls\":0,\"deleteCalls\":1}\nDREAMS.md excerpt:\nDREAMS.md first line: Dream Diary\n\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:diary:start -->\n---\n\n*May 7, 2026 at 10:00 AM UTC*\n\nsome memory from a completed dreaming phase\n\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:diary:end -->\n\n\n=== ok-but-no-assistant-text ===\nworkspace=/tmp/openclaw-pr78698-ok-but-no-assistant-text-JmgbOG\ndreams_before=false\n[subagent] run sessionKey=dreaming-narrative-rem-c3823da03563-1778148000000 mode=default\n[subagent] waitForRun runId=proof-run-1 timeoutMs=60000\n[subagent] getSessionMessages sessionKey=dreaming-narrative-rem-c3823da03563-1778148000000 limit=5\n[ok-but-no-assistant-text] warn: memory-core: narrative generation produced no text for rem phase; writing fallback diary entry.\n[ok-but-no-assistant-text] info: memory-core: narrative generation used fallback for rem phase because the narrative run produced no text.\n[subagent] deleteSession sessionKey=dreaming-narrative-rem-c3823da03563-1778148000000\ndreams_after=true\ndreams_bytes=168\ndiary_block_present=true\nfallback_entry_uses_phase_snippet=true\nsubagent_stats={\"runCalls\":1,\"waitCalls\":1,\"getMessagesCalls\":1,\"deleteCalls\":1}\nDREAMS.md excerpt:\nDREAMS.md first line: Dream Diary\n\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:diary:start -->\n---\n\n*May 7, 2026 at 10:00 AM UTC*\n\npattern surfaced from recall candidates\n\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:diary:end -->\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: In both terminal cases, `dreams_before=false` and `dreams_after=true`; the runtime log says it is \"writing fallback diary entry\" / \"used fallback\", `diary_block_present=true`, and the copied `DREAMS.md` excerpts show the appended Dream Diary block.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full overnight cron scheduling was not run in this proof; the proof directly exercises the memory-core narrative writer path that cron calls.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `node scripts/test-extension.mjs memory-core -- extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory-events.test.ts` — 53 files passed, 611 passed",
